## Strongest unsupported assumption

> {{STRONGEST_UNSUPPORTED_ASSUMPTION}}

This is the claim that, if wrong, would most break this plan. Name it explicitly. If research later falsifies it, this plan is invalidated — flip trigger below.

**How to find it:** Look at the Phase 5 plan and ask: "What am I most confident in that I actually have no evidence for?" Common candidates:
- An assumption about what the user needs (from Phase 2) that was never verified against real use
- A structural choice (e.g., separate sections for decisions vs open questions) that assumes a mental model the user may not share
- A quality dimension that seemed obvious but has no research backing

If you cannot name the strongest unsupported assumption: you haven't looked hard enough. Produce at least one candidate. Name the CLAIM, not just the uncertainty.

**Flip trigger:** If {{CONDITION_THAT_INVALIDATES_ASSUMPTION}}, revise plan before continuing to Phase 6.

