## File manifest

Every file that will be produced in Phase 6. No file gets built that isn't here. No file here gets skipped without logging the skip and reason.

Order: riskiest/highest-stakes files first (from Phase 3 research synthesis).

| # | File | Purpose | Done-criteria | Stakes |
|---|------|---------|---------------|--------|
| 1 | `CLAUDE.md` *(behavioral contract — ALWAYS FIRST)* | Goal-directed advisor behavior for the agent using this kit | Contains: gold standard, agent-owns/user-owns delegation model, after-every-task rule, proactive surfacing rule, decay warning | HIGH |
| 2 | `ENTRYPOINT.md` | Execution contract for the kit | Agent can start from this file alone and reach all other files without producer help | HIGH |
| 3 | {{FILE_3}} | {{PURPOSE_3}} | {{DONE_CRITERIA_3}} | {{STAKES_3}} |
| … | … | … | … | … |

**Ordering rule:** File #1 is always the behavioral contract. Non-negotiable. If riskiest-first ordering would place a different file first: the behavioral contract still goes first. Riskiest-first applies to all files from #2 onward.

### Done-criteria format

Each done-criterion must be testable without running the kit. Acceptable forms:
- "File contains X" / "File does not contain X"
- "Agent reading only this file can perform action Y"
- "Auditor (read-only) can verify claim Z from this file alone"

Not acceptable: "is complete", "is high quality", "covers the domain well"

